.TH "afu_dma_map_region" 9 "afu_dma_map_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
afu_dma_map_region \- map memory region for dma
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" afu_dma_map_region
.BI "(struct dfl_feature_platform_data *pdata "  ","
.BI "u64 user_addr "  ","
.BI "u64 length "  ","
.BI "u64 *iova "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdata" 12
feature device platform data
.IP "user_addr" 12
address of the memory region
.IP "length" 12
size of the memory region
.IP "iova" 12
pointer of iova address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Map memory region defined by \fIuser_addr\fP and \fIlength\fP, and return dma address
of the memory region via \fIiova\fP.
Return 0 for success, otherwise error code.
